dellNetIpForwardMib.name: dellNetIpForwardMib

revisions.description: This version of MIB module deprecates the dellNetIpForwardTable and replaces it with dellNetInetCidrRouteTable which adds the IP Protocol Independance
Initial version of this MIB module.

dellNetIpForwardMib.description: This MIB module is used to display CIDR multipath IP Routes.

chSysCardNumber.name: chSysCardNumber
chSysCardNumber.description: This is the card number assigned to the line cards and the RPM cards in the chassis. The line cards number are from 0 to 13 and the RPM are from 0 to 1.

dellNetIpForwardVersionTable.name: dellNetIpForwardVersionTable
dellNetIpForwardVersionTable.description: This entity's IP forward version table.

dellNetIpForwardVersionEntry.name: dellNetIpForwardVersionEntry
dellNetIpForwardVersionEntry.description: The row definition for the ip forward version Table.

dellNetIpForwardAddrFamily.name: dellNetIpForwardAddrFamily
dellNetIpForwardAddrFamily.description: Address Family of the IP Forwarding Table for which this entry provides the Version information.

dellNetIpForwardVersion.name: dellNetIpForwardVersion
dellNetIpForwardVersion.description: A version number on the Forwarding Table. This is always fetched from one line card.

dellNetIpForwardEntry.name: dellNetIpForwardEntry
dellNetIpForwardEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination, under a particular policy.

dellNetIpforwardDest.name: dellNetIpforwardDest
dellNetIpforwardDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route.

dellNetIpforwardMask.name: dellNetIpforwardMask
dellNetIpforwardMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the dellNetIpforwardDest field.

dellNetIpforwardNextHop.name: dellNetIpforwardNextHop
dellNetIpforwardNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route; Otherwise, 0.0.0.0.

dellNetIpforwardFirstHop.name: dellNetIpforwardFirstHop
dellNetIpforwardFirstHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the Gateway to the nexthop; 0.0.0.0 if the Nexthop itself is a Gateway to the Destination

dellNetIpforwardIfIndex.name: dellNetIpforwardIfIndex
dellNetIpforwardIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

dellNetIpforwardMacAddress.name: dellNetIpforwardMacAddress
dellNetIpforwardMacAddress.description: The Mac address of the NextHop.

dellNetIpforwardEgressPort.name: dellNetIpforwardEgressPort
dellNetIpforwardEgressPort.description: The name of the egress port to which the packets will be forwarded.

dellNetIpforwardCamIndex.name: dellNetIpforwardCamIndex
dellNetIpforwardCamIndex.description: Cam Entry corresponding to a row.

dellNetInetCidrIpv4RouteNumber.name: dellNetInetCidrIpv4RouteNumber
dellNetInetCidrIpv4RouteNumber.description: The number of current dellNetInetCidrRouteTable entries that are not Invalid and whose dellNetInetCidrRouteDestType is ipv4(1)

dellNetInetCidrIpv6RouteNumber.name: dellNetInetCidrIpv6RouteNumber
dellNetInetCidrIpv6RouteNumber.description: The number of current dellNetInetCidrRouteTable entries that are not Invalid and whose dellNetInetCidrRouteDestType is ipv6(2)

dellNetInetCidrRouteTableEntry.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteTableEntry
dellNetInetCidrRouteTableEntry.description: A particular route to a particular destination Implementers need to be aware that if the total number of elements (octets or sub-identifiers) in inetCidrRouteDest, inetCidrRoutePolicy, and inetCidrRouteNextHop exceeds 111, then OIDs of column instances in this table will have more than 128 sub- identifiers and cannot be accessed using SNMPv1, SNMPv2c, or SNMPv3. For S-Series Platform, Value of chSysCardNumber will always be zero

dellNetInetCidrRouteDestType.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteDestType
dellNetInetCidrRouteDestType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteDest address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

dellNetInetCidrRouteDest.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteDest
dellNetInetCidrRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteDestType object.

dellNetInetCidrRoutePfxLen.name: dellNetInetCidrRoutePfxLen
dellNetInetCidrRoutePfxLen.description: Indicates the number of leading one bits that form the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the inetCidrRouteDest field.

dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHopType.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHopType
dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHopType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteNextHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Value should be set to unknown(0) for non-remote routes. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHop.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHop
dellNetInetCidrRouteNextHop.description: On remote routes, the address of the next system en route. For non-remote routes, a zero length string. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteNextHopType object.

dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHopType.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHopType
dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHopType.description: The type of the inetCidrRouteFirstHop address, as defined in the InetAddress MIB. Value should be set to unknown(0) for non-remote routes. Only those address types that may appear in an actual routing table are allowed as values of this object.

dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHop.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHop
dellNetInetCidrRouteFirstHop.description: The address of the gateway to the Nexthop. If the nexthop itself is the gateway, a zero length string. The type of this address is determined by the value of the inetCidrRouteFirstHopType object.

dellNetInetCidrRouteIfIndex.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteIfIndex
dellNetInetCidrRouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value that identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. A value of 0 is valid and represents the scenario where no interface is specified.

dellNetInetCidrRouteMacAddress.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteMacAddress
dellNetInetCidrRouteMacAddress.description: The Mac address of the NextHop.

dellNetInetCidrRouteEgressPort.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteEgressPort
dellNetInetCidrRouteEgressPort.description: The name of the egress port to which the packets will be forwarded.

dellNetInetCidrRouteCamIndex.name: dellNetInetCidrRouteCamIndex
dellNetInetCidrRouteCamIndex.description: Cam Entry corresponding to a row.

dellNetIpForwardMibCompliance.name: dellNetIpForwardMibCompliance
dellNetIpForwardMibCompliance.description: The basic implementation requirements for the Dell Networking OS Ip Forward MIB.

dellNetIpForwardObjectGroup.name: dellNetIpForwardObjectGroup
dellNetIpForwardObjectGroup.description: Objects for the IP aware Route Table.
